1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT REMOVING THE CAP ON SATELLITE ANNEXATIONS FOR THE TOWNS OF
3 BAILEY AND WEAVERVILLE AND THE CITY OF CHERRYVILLE AND
4 DEANNEXING CERTAIN DESCRIBED PROPERTY FROM THE CORPORATE
5 LIMITS OF THE TOWN OF VASS.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7
8 TOWNS OF BAILEY AND WEAVERVILLE/CITY OF CHERRYVILLE SATELLITE
9 ANNEXATION CAP REMOVAL
10 SECTION 1. G.S. 160A-58.1(b) reads as rewritten:
11 "(b) A noncontiguous area proposed for annexation must meet all of the following
12 standards:
13 …
14 (5) The area within the proposed satellite corporate limits, when added to the area
15 within all other satellite corporate limits, may not exceed ten percent (10%)
16 of the area within the primary corporate limits of the annexing city.
17 This subdivision does not apply to the Cities of Archdale, Asheboro,
18 Belmont, Cherryville, Claremont, Concord, Conover, Durham, Elizabeth
19 City, Gastonia, Greenville, Hickory, Kannapolis, Kings Mountain, Locust,
20 Lowell, Marion, Mount Airy, Mount Holly, New Bern, Newton, Oxford,
21 Randleman, Roanoke Rapids, Rockingham, Saluda, Sanford, Salisbury,
22 Shelby, Southport, Statesville, and Washington and the Towns of Ahoskie,
23 Angier, Apex, Ayden, Bailey, Belville, Benson, Bladenboro, Bridgeton,
24 Bunn, Burgaw, Calabash, Carthage, Catawba, China Grove, Clayton,
25 Columbia, Columbus, Cramerton, Creswell, Dallas, Dobson, Four Oaks,
26 Franklin, Franklinton, Franklinville, Fuquay-Varina, Garner, Godwin,
27 Goldston, Granite Quarry, Green Level, Grimesland, Harrisburg, Holly Ridge,
28 Holly Springs, Hookerton, Hope Mills, Huntersville, Jamestown, Kenansville,
29 Kenly, Knightdale, Landis, Laurel Park, Liberty, Lillington, Louisburg,
